stories.text:
Hi HN, I'm a junior/mid-experienced (3 years of experience) ML engineer with experience in ML in general but more specifically in NLP. For some reasons, I cannot change jobs at the time being, and at the same time I'd need an extra income.

What are ways to leverage my ML/NLP knowledge to earn extra money on the side? Ideally, something that doesn't imply coding (unless it's a one time thing to get some sort of passive income), since my main job already burns me out programming-wise. Could I get paid to give advice to startups? What about teaching (how and where)?

Thank you in advance!
stories.title: Ask HN: How do I earn money on the side as a ML engineer?
